📊 **Customer Service Request Analysis**

This project focuses on analyzing customer service requests data to identify patterns, trends, and key insights. The dataset includes various complaint types across different cities, along with response and resolution times.

The analysis involves data cleaning, exploratory data analysis (EDA), and statistical testing to understand service efficiency and complaint behavior. Key insights highlight the most frequent complaint types, city-wise distribution, and variations in response time.

Statistical methods such as ANOVA and Kruskal-Wallis tests are applied to determine significant differences in response times across complaint categories. 

🔹 **Key Features:**

* Data Cleaning & Preprocessing
* Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
* Complaint Type Analysis
* City-wise Complaint Distribution
* Response Time Analysis
* Statistical Testing (p-value, Kruskal-Wallis)
* Insight Generation

🔹 **Tools & Technologies:**

* Python (Pandas, NumPy)
* Data Visualization (Matplotlib, Seaborn)
* Statistical Analysis (SciPy)

🔹 **Outcome:**
Identified major complaint patterns, high-frequency issues like noise and illegal parking, and significant differences in response times across complaint types.
